+# Data Availability
+
+## Copyright-limited verbatim excerpt
+
+> Data used in this study are publicly available at the Zenodo repository
+
+Full verbatim reproduction is deferred because this run must keep source quotation short. Evidence: The publisher statement points to the Zenodo record and lists Windturbines database, MCD12Q1, GEOS-5, Maritime Boundaries Geodatabase, terrestrial and marine ecological reserve masks, SRTM GES and MERRA-2.
+
+## Structural classification
+
+| Check | Status | Evidence |
+|---|---|---|
+| Has dataset DOI or repository record | Yes | Evidence: The statement points to `https://zenodo.org/record/7963012#.ZGzUd31Bw2w`. |
+| Has repository | Yes | Evidence: Zenodo is used for study data. |
+| Has on-request clause | No | Evidence: No on-request clause appears in the publisher Data Availability text. |
+| Source Data file | Not identified in Zotero | Evidence: The article page lists Supplementary Information and Peer Review File, while the pre-extraction hint lists main PDF and SI. |
+| FAIR-compliance assessment | Medium | Inference: Confidence medium. The statement gives a public archive and source URLs, but this run did not independently check file-level metadata or license fields in Zenodo. |
+
+## Lesson for my own DA statements
+
+Lesson: Put the model archive first, then list each external input dataset with stable URLs. For Henry's work, add a one-line file map so readers know which archive file supports which figure.
